<concept id="concept_B32294CC9FA643A2A14A74B1DAA49C95" xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>Creating a Certificate Signing Request </title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p>Create a certificate signing request (CSR) by executing the following command: </p>
            <p>
                <codeblock>%JAVA_HOME%\bin\keytool -certreq -alias tpcert -file tpcert.csr 
-keystore keystore.jks</codeblock>
            </p>
            <p>The alias <codeph>tpcert</codeph> refers to the created certificate. The result of the above command is a file name <codeph>tpcert.csr</codeph>. Send this file to the certification authority (CA), for example, the <ph
                    conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/> operator.</p>
        </section>
    </conbody>
</concept>
